# Multi-node Minikube(Control Plane + Worker Nodes in Minikube)

Reality check: Can Minikube create master–slave?
-> Default Minikube ❌ 
-> ONLY ONE NODE (Control Plane + Worker in same VM)
-> Minikube can simulate master + workers using multiple nodes.

---

Step 1: Delete old cluster (recommended)
minikube delete

---

Step 2: Start Minikube with multiple nodes (based on your need)
minikube start --nodes=2
(or)
minikube start --nodes=3

---

Step 3: Verify nodes
kubectl get nodes

You will see something like:

minikube        Ready   control-plane
minikube-m02    Ready   <none>

✔ minikube → Control Plane
✔ minikube-m02 → Worker Node

🎉 Master–Worker setup achieved

---

Step 4: Label nodes for clarity (Optional) 
kubectl label node minikube role=master
kubectl label node minikube-m02 role=worker

Check:

kubectl get nodes --show-labels

---

// Some theory for understanding
How scheduling works now (IMPORTANT)

Control Plane runs:

kube-apiserver

scheduler

controller-manager

Worker runs:

kubelet

kube-proxy

Pods

You can verify:

kubectl get pods -n kube-system -o wide

--- 

Extra: Want pods ONLY on worker node? (Advanced but useful)
Step 1: Taint control plane
kubectl taint nodes minikube node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane=:NoSchedule

Step 2: Deploy a pod

Now pods will schedule only on worker node.

